value.title: Live Updates: Biden to Speak on Economy Hours After Senate Approves Relief Package
value.excerpt: President Biden and Vice President Harris plan to meet with House Democratic leaders Friday morning to discuss the stimulus package. The Senate approved Mr. Biden’s plan but knocked out the $15 minimum wage.

value.title: 'America is back' - Biden touts muscular foreign policy in first diplomatic speech
value.excerpt: U.S. President Joe Biden on Thursday promised a new era after the scattershot foreign policy of his predecessor, Donald Trump, declaring "America is back" on the global stage in his first diplomatic address as president.

value.title: Congressional Democrats propose up to $50,000 in debt cancelation, Biden not sold
value.excerpt: Congressional Democrats renewed calls Thursday for President Joe Biden to cancel up to $50,000 in federal student loans per individual.

value.title: Sen. Ben Sasse slams Nebraska GOP committee’s plans to censure him for criticizing Trump
value.excerpt: Sasse is the latest Republican to face censure or the threat of it from a state or local GOP for not supporting Trump.

value.title: Biden to call for protecting LGBTQ rights globally in memo
value.excerpt: It reflects his deep commitment to these issues both here in the United States and everywhere around the world," national security adviser Jake Sullivan said.

value.title: Chief of staff: White House hopes to revive Trump plan to mail masks to Americans
value.excerpt: The Biden administration is hoping to resurrect a proposal from the Trump administration to mail face masks to every American in an attempt to stop the spread of Covid-19, White House chief of staff Ron Klain said Thursday.

value.title: Pompeo on Biden declaring 'America is back': 'Back to when ISIS controlled a caliphate'?
value.excerpt: Former Secretary of State Mike Pompeo reacted Thursday to President Biden's declaration that "America is back" by asking if the commander-in-chief meant "back to when ISIS controlled a caliphate in Syria that was the size of Britain."

value.title: Pence reveals his post-White House plans
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence is joining the Heritage Foundation as a distinguished fellow, according to three people familiar with the matter. The move comes a day after the former vice president launched his transition office and announced plans to relocate to his home state of Indiana this summer.

value.title: ‘We’ve learned to love the guy:’ How Biden charmed the left
value.excerpt: It’s early, but progressive say they’re being included, heard and respected by the Biden White House. But rocky roads are still ahead.

value.title: France's leader "very upset" by platforms' muzzling of Trump
value.excerpt: French President Emmanuel Macron says he was “very upset” by the way social networks muzzled Donald Trump at the tail end of his U.S. presidency

value.title: Voting company sues Fox and Trump lawyers for $2.7bn over false claims of election fraud
value.excerpt: Smartmatic lawsuit charges that the defendants conspired to spread false claims that the company helped ‘steal’ the US election

value.title: Pelosi rejects Trump impeachment acquittal, says Senate will reveal 'cowards or courage'
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi, D-Calif., rejected any notion that former President Trump is headed for a second acquittal in the Senate during his impeachment trial.

value.title: Mike Pence to join Heritage Foundation as distinguished visiting fellow
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence is joining the Heritage Foundation as a distinguished visiting fellow, according to a press release from the conservative think tank.

value.title: Pence joining Heritage Foundation as distinguished fellow
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence is joining the Heritage Foundation, one of the oldest and most influential think tanks in the conservative movement.

value.title: Biden priority is 'dealing with China's trade abuses' that harm American workers: National security adviser
value.excerpt: White House National Security Adviser Jake Sullivan said a "priority" of the Biden administration is "dealing with China’s trade abuses" that harm American workers, adding that President Biden’s national security strategy will lead with "diplomacy."

value.title: Hunter Biden's memoir 'Beautiful Things' out in April
value.excerpt: NEW YORK (AP) —

value.title: Sanders, Ocasio-Cortez, and Blumenauer unveil bill pushing Biden to declare national climate emergency: 'We are out of time'
value.excerpt: Three progressive lawmakers introduced legislation Thursday that would require President Joe Biden to declare a national climate emergency, arguing that the US is "out of time and excuses" to deal with the climate crisis.

value.title: Trump resigns from Screen Actors Guild: ‘I no longer wish to be associated with your union’
value.excerpt: President Trump is resigning from the Screen Actors Guild - American Federation of Television and Radio Artists after they threatened to expel his membership from the union after the Capitol riot -- to which he said, “Who cares!”

value.title: White House to leave any intelligence requests from Trump to intel community
value.excerpt: The Biden White House says the intelligence community will review any incoming requests for intelligence briefings from former President Donald Trump, as has been customary for former presidents, though he has not yet made any.

value.title: Biden focuses on faith and unity during 'dark, dark time' in prayer breakfast remarks
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden on Thursday cited the importance of unity and faith during what he described as a "dark, dark time" for many Americans, as he continued the presidential tradition of participation in the National Prayer Breakfast.

value.title: Biden addresses National Prayer Breakfast, says 'we need to defeat political extremism'
value.excerpt: President Biden addressed the National Prayer Breakfast on Thursday, saying the country needs to "defeat political extremism" and rely on "faith to guide us out of the darkness and into the light" amid the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: Biden, at prayer breakfast, calls out ‘political extremism’
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden has called for a confrontation of the “political extremism” that inspired the U.S. Capitol riot in remarks at the National Prayer Breakfast

value.title: U.S. Treasury says more time needed to decide on Trump tax returns - Bloomberg News
value.excerpt: The U.S. Treasury said it needs more time to decide whether to fight House Democrats in their effort to get former President Donald Trump's personal and business tax returns, Bloomberg News reported on Wednesday.

value.title: Maxine Waters says Trump should be charged with 'premeditated murder'
value.excerpt: Democratic Rep. Maxine Waters of California Tuesday said she thinks former President Donald Trump should be charged with "premeditated murder" over the deadly riots at the U.S. Capitol on Jan. 6.

value.title: Former VP Pence opens transition office in northern Virginia
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence has opened a transition office in northern Virginia.
